    "(Note: A grandmother is called jeje maa, maa, or burhi maa, not \"Aaita. \")",
    "-She referred to her aunt as Phuphaji.",
    "(Note: \"Phuphaji\" refers to a male relative -father's sister's husband -so it cannot mean \"aunt. \")",
    "-They affectionately addressed their elders as Deuta and Aita.",
    "(Note: \"Deuta\" and \"Aita\" words are not related to the Bodo Community.)"
